HEADWORD: nonsubjective
<hw>nonsubjective</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>undistorted by emotion or
personal bias; based on observable phenomena; objective. Opposite of
<ant>subjective</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>clinical, detached,
unemotional</stype>; <stype>impersonal, neutral</stype>;
<stype>verifiable </stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> objective.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

